{"pagelen": 50, "values": [{"update": {"description": "Similar for what we do in [sdformat](https://bitbucket.org/osrf/sdformat/pull-request/173/convert-to-use-ignition-math/diff#chg-configure.bat) when using the ignition-math zip, we can not use the cmake module. configure.bat is in charge of inject the variables directly.\r\n\r\n* Testing run on [default branch](http://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo-any-devel-windows7-amd64/25/)\r\n* Testing run on [this branch](http://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo-any-devel-windows7-amd64/27/console). Still need more fixes.", "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "c310efdb4421", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/commit/c310efdb4421.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/commits/c310efdb4421"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "branch": {"name": "default"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "7a7c3b17b0c9", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/commit/7a7c3b17b0c9.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/commits/7a7c3b17b0c9"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "branch": {"name": "fix_configure_for_ignmath"}}, "state": "MERGED", "author": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0/ca24bb11-4787-4b14-a20d-d91835e9bde2/128"}}, "nickname": "Nathan Koenig", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0"}, "date": "2015-06-19T14:15:42.470719+00:00"}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"approval": {"date": "2015-06-19T14:15:19.275184+00:00", "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "user": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0/ca24bb11-4787-4b14-a20d-d91835e9bde2/128"}}, "nickname": "Nathan Koenig", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0"}}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"approval": {"date": "2015-06-18T22:57:08.447975+00:00", "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7648029.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7648029"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "Thanks very much @chrisdembia @traversaro  for the information on relocatable cmake modules, seems to me like the way to go. Just need to check how it affects to debian packages and how to migrate all our software modules to it. I've created an issue in [ign-math](https://bitbucket.org/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/issue/24/migrate-to-relocatable-cmake-module) and I will add it to my task list.\n\nI maintain this pull request still in place, since it will help during the transition and allow me to add Windows to our CI cycle. ", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Thanks very much @chrisdembia @traversaro  for the information on relocatable cmake modules, seems to me like the way to go. Just need to check how it affects to debian packages and how to migrate all our software modules to it. I've created an issue in <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://bitbucket.org/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/issue/24/migrate-to-relocatable-cmake-module\" rel=\"nofollow\">ign-math</a> and I will add it to my task list.</p>\n<p>I maintain this pull request still in place, since it will help during the transition and allow me to add Windows to our CI cycle. </p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-18T22:50:10.375121+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-18T22:50:10.452030+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7648029}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7647987.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7647987"}}, "parent": {"id": 7614823, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7614823.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7614823"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "Thanks Silvio, that sounds ideal to me. Time to work on it.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Thanks Silvio, that sounds ideal to me. Time to work on it.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-18T22:47:36.140816+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-18T22:47:36.149606+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7647987}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7646790.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7646790"}}, "parent": {"id": 7645868, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7645868.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7645868"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "Thanks for explaining. Let me know if you guys have other questions.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Thanks for explaining. Let me know if you guys have other questions.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-18T21:41:50.920701+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Christopher Dembia", "uuid": "{a746cc7a-c30a-436f-b56f-8a773034e093}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Ba746cc7a-c30a-436f-b56f-8a773034e093%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Ba746cc7a-c30a-436f-b56f-8a773034e093%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:f1a7d88e-3453-4a30-8cc6-dece080e6874/8cda6057-d9e9-4851-9ad4-14d81b91cdaf/128"}}, "nickname": "chrisdembia", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:f1a7d88e-3453-4a30-8cc6-dece080e6874"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-18T21:41:50.982326+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7646790}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7645868.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7645868"}}, "parent": {"id": 7606219, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7606219.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7606219"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "Chris, configure.bat is just a custom hardcoded script that help us to inject all the paths expected by gazebo for handling dependencies, specially all the dependencies get using pkgconfig. It has been useful but it is far from being ideal.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Chris, configure.bat is just a custom hardcoded script that help us to inject all the paths expected by gazebo for handling dependencies, specially all the dependencies get using pkgconfig. It has been useful but it is far from being ideal.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-18T21:04:39.100230+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-18T21:04:39.109602+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7645868}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7614823.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7614823"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "In Yarp binary distribution in Windows, we just copy the relocatable `**Config.cmake` (as explained by @chrisdembia ) in the installer. \n\nThe cool thing is that if you install the library to some specific system paths (the one contained in `CMAKE_SYSTEM_PREFIX_PATH`) and the \n`**Config.cmake` are contained in the project directories with a given structure (as documented in the [\n  find_package](http://www.cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.0/command/find_package.html) documentation) you don't need to define \nany specific environmental variable to find the installed libraries.\n\n Furthermore, even if you install  all the projects in a non-system location, you just to add the installation prefix  to \nthe `CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH` and you will find automatically all the packages installed in that location, without\nhardcoding any path in the `configure.bat` file (or just hardcoding there the `CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH`) . \n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>In Yarp binary distribution in Windows, we just copy the relocatable <code>**Config.cmake</code> (as explained by @chrisdembia ) in the installer. </p>\n<p>The cool thing is that if you install the library to some specific system paths (the one contained in <code>CMAKE_SYSTEM_PREFIX_PATH</code>) and the \n<code>**Config.cmake</code> are contained in the project directories with a given structure (as documented in the <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://www.cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.0/command/find_package.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">\n  find_package</a> documentation) you don't need to define \nany specific environmental variable to find the installed libraries.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, even if you install  all the projects in a non-system location, you just to add the installation prefix  to \nthe <code>CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH</code> and you will find automatically all the packages installed in that location, without\nhardcoding any path in the <code>configure.bat</code> file (or just hardcoding there the <code>CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH</code>) . </p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-17T23:37:08.286107+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Silvio Traversaro", "uuid": "{34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:e1c3e6a0-9a64-4e5f-a668-feebc191c5b6/578caaa1-056c-45a2-8bf9-bee94c3bebef/128"}}, "nickname": "traversaro", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e1c3e6a0-9a64-4e5f-a668-feebc191c5b6"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-17T23:38:29.579442+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7614823}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7606219.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7606219"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "Elena (elen4 on GitHub) built upon the fantastic SimbodyConfig.cmake that you guys wrote for us and has made Simbody re-locatable (at least as far as CMake is concerned). So, the installed SimbodyConfig.cmake does not contain any hardcoded paths. Here is Elena's pull request that achieved this: https://github.com/simbody/simbody/pull/356\n\nI have also done the same relocatability for OpenSim: https://github.com/opensim-org/opensim-core/commit/80c74f140bf382fc77c57e395fe3193e032336b6\n\nThe end of this page (http://www.cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.0/module/CMakePackageConfigHelpers.html) explains what to do.\n\nThe only *real* reason that it was necessary to do this was that, on Windows, the OpenSim installer lets the user choose their installation directory, and so we don't know the installation directory at build time. \n\nSo if what you are looking for is a way to use CMake Config files to make your binary package relocatable, then this is exactly what you're looking for.  However, I don't know how configure.bat relates to CMake Config files.\n\nCan you tell me what configure.bat does, where it comes from or what/who generates it?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Elena (elen4 on GitHub) built upon the fantastic SimbodyConfig.cmake that you guys wrote for us and has made Simbody re-locatable (at least as far as CMake is concerned). So, the installed SimbodyConfig.cmake does not contain any hardcoded paths. Here is Elena's pull request that achieved this: <a href=\"https://github.com/simbody/simbody/pull/356\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">https://github.com/simbody/simbody/pull/356</a></p>\n<p>I have also done the same relocatability for OpenSim: <a href=\"https://github.com/opensim-org/opensim-core/commit/80c74f140bf382fc77c57e395fe3193e032336b6\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">https://github.com/opensim-org/opensim-core/commit/80c74f140bf382fc77c57e395fe3193e032336b6</a></p>\n<p>The end of this page (<a href=\"http://www.cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.0/module/CMakePackageConfigHelpers.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">http://www.cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.0/module/CMakePackageConfigHelpers.html</a>) explains what to do.</p>\n<p>The only <em>real</em> reason that it was necessary to do this was that, on Windows, the OpenSim installer lets the user choose their installation directory, and so we don't know the installation directory at build time. </p>\n<p>So if what you are looking for is a way to use CMake Config files to make your binary package relocatable, then this is exactly what you're looking for.  However, I don't know how configure.bat relates to CMake Config files.</p>\n<p>Can you tell me what configure.bat does, where it comes from or what/who generates it?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-17T17:25:32.845755+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Christopher Dembia", "uuid": "{a746cc7a-c30a-436f-b56f-8a773034e093}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Ba746cc7a-c30a-436f-b56f-8a773034e093%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Ba746cc7a-c30a-436f-b56f-8a773034e093%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:f1a7d88e-3453-4a30-8cc6-dece080e6874/8cda6057-d9e9-4851-9ad4-14d81b91cdaf/128"}}, "nickname": "chrisdembia", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:f1a7d88e-3453-4a30-8cc6-dece080e6874"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-17T18:42:07.346837+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7606219}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7603880.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7603880"}}, "parent": {"id": 7601954, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7601954.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7601954"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "Jose, I'm not sure exactly what OpenSim does and I think @chrisdembia improved it recently. When OpenSim is distributed in binary it includes a local copy of Simbody's binaries and hence avoids installation problems. I'm not sure that would make any sense for Gazebo, but making anything robust on Windows can be very difficult. Chris may be able to provide more useful information.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Jose, I'm not sure exactly what OpenSim does and I think @chrisdembia improved it recently. When OpenSim is distributed in binary it includes a local copy of Simbody's binaries and hence avoids installation problems. I'm not sure that would make any sense for Gazebo, but making anything robust on Windows can be very difficult. Chris may be able to provide more useful information.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-17T16:09:31.951654+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Sherman", "uuid": "{997c6f1e-e2a3-4f0e-8fa4-fed745840d50}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B997c6f1e-e2a3-4f0e-8fa4-fed745840d50%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B997c6f1e-e2a3-4f0e-8fa4-fed745840d50%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/355dea43ed612b7be3c9361df2d52213d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsMS-2.png"}}, "nickname": "sherm1", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:4590c319-b75f-4187-93d4-6cec61da74f7"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-17T16:09:31.961879+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7603880}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7603285.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7603285"}}, "parent": {"id": 7601954, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7601954.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7601954"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "the opensim source code is [here](https://github.com/opensim-org/opensim-core)", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>the opensim source code is <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://github.com/opensim-org/opensim-core\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-17T15:53:44.325741+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-17T15:53:44.335980+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7603285}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7601954.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7601954"}}, "parent": {"id": 7573287, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7573287.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7573287"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "In our case, in the current generated zip for ignition-math [we are hardcoding the full paths](https://bitbucket.org/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/src/83baead60039d607100c9d5a84ca7322c935ca5a/cmake/ignition-math-config.cmake.in?at=default#cl-6) to libraries and headers at the moment of compiling, so when re-distributing to another machine, and change the installation directory, it can not work anymore. I did not investigate if this paths can be relative.\n\n@sherm1 opensim is using a precompiled Simbody package or zip? If so, where I can find it? In the case of opensim is compiling simbody, then the paths are in sync with the filesystem, so that can be the reason why the whole thing works.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>In our case, in the current generated zip for ignition-math <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://bitbucket.org/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/src/83baead60039d607100c9d5a84ca7322c935ca5a/cmake/ignition-math-config.cmake.in?at=default#cl-6\" rel=\"nofollow\">we are hardcoding the full paths</a> to libraries and headers at the moment of compiling, so when re-distributing to another machine, and change the installation directory, it can not work anymore. I did not investigate if this paths can be relative.</p>\n<p>@sherm1 opensim is using a precompiled Simbody package or zip? If so, where I can find it? In the case of opensim is compiling simbody, then the paths are in sync with the filesystem, so that can be the reason why the whole thing works.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-17T15:20:19.329904+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-17T15:20:19.393629+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7601954}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7573699.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7573699"}}, "parent": {"id": 7573287, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7573287.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7573287"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "That's true.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>That's true.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-16T18:45:12.005388+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Sherman", "uuid": "{997c6f1e-e2a3-4f0e-8fa4-fed745840d50}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B997c6f1e-e2a3-4f0e-8fa4-fed745840d50%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B997c6f1e-e2a3-4f0e-8fa4-fed745840d50%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/355dea43ed612b7be3c9361df2d52213d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsMS-2.png"}}, "nickname": "sherm1", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:4590c319-b75f-4187-93d4-6cec61da74f7"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-16T18:45:12.013737+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7573699}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733/comments/7573287.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733/_/diff#comment-7573287"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1733.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1733"}}, "title": "Fix configure.bat for ignition-math zip"}, "content": {"raw": "Do you know why we can't use the cmake module? I believe opensim uses cmake to find simbody on Windows.\n\n@sherm1 ", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Do you know why we can't use the cmake module? I believe opensim uses cmake to find simbody on Windows.</p>\n<p>@sherm1 </p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-06-16T18:31:02.173508+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": "2015-06-16T18:31:02.194602+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 7573287}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1733, "links": 